e clusters, admission validation, network policy, and service mesh.</blockquote><p>How to run StageSet without granting it broad cluster power, keep secrets
encrypted, and constrain what it can reach. The controller applies as a tenant
<code>ServiceAccount</code>, so a StageSet can do exactly what its RBAC allows and no more.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong><a href="/security/encryption/">Secrets encryption</a>
</strong> — decrypt SOPS-encrypted files
in memory during apply.</li>
<li><strong><a href="/security/multi-cluster/">Multi-cluster and tenancy</a>
</strong> — apply as a tenant
<code>ServiceAccount</code> or to a remote cluster.</li>
<li><strong><a href="/security/admission-webhook/">Admission webhook</a>
</strong> — validate StageSets at
admission time.</li>
<li><strong><a href="/security/network-policy/">Network policy</a>
</strong> — lock the controller&rsquo;s traffic
down to what it needs.</li>
<li><strong><a href="/security/service-mesh/">Service mesh</a>
</strong> — run the controller inside a mesh.
</content></li>
</ul>
